  <static seed="1169" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/reduceRationalFunction10.pg">
    <statement><p>Simplify the function formula, and if applicable, write the restricted domain.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ G(y) = {\frac{y-2}{y^{2}-9y+14}} }</m></p>
<p>Reduced <m>G(y)=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\frac{1}{y-7}, y\ne 2</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To simplify the expression, we first factor both the numerator and denominator, and then cancel common factors.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
   G(y) \amp = {\frac{y-2}{y^{2}-9y+14}} \\
                 \amp = \frac{{y-2}}{{\left(y-2\right)\mathopen{}\left(y-7\right)}} \\
                 \amp = {\frac{1}{y-7}, y\ne 2}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Since the factor <m>y - 2</m> was canceled, the domain condition lost during the reduction is <m>y \ne 2</m>.</p>
</solution>
